                    <history>
                        <origin>Possibly completed in the <origPlace cert="medium"
                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208" key="place_7000208"
                                >Indian subcontinent</origPlace> undated, but possibly <origDate
                                cert="medium" calendar="#Gregorian" from="1699" to="1800"
                                >18th-century</origDate>.</origin>
                        <provenance><p>While the circumstances under which this manuscript arrived
                            in Britain remain unclear, British East India Company writer
                                    <persName role="fmo ins ato">Robert Thomas Ives
                                    (1763–1786)</persName>, the son of naval surgeon <persName
                                    role="asn" key="person_2822066"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/2822066">Edward Ives
                                    (1719–1786)</persName> whom in 1773 published an account of his
                                voyage to India and overland return. Whether Robert also travelled to India and returned with the volume awaits confirmation.</p></provenance>
                        <provenance><p>Manchester bookseller <persName
                                    role="bsl" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/"
                                    key="person_98861310">J. E. Cornish</persName> subsequently
                                acquired the manuscript from an unidentified source.</p></provenance>
                        <acquisition>
